n. The study or knowledge of antiquities, esp. of
   prehistoric antiquities; a discourse or treatise on antiquities;
   archaeology .

a. Having no term or end; unlimited; boundless; unending;
   as, termless time.
a. Inexpressible; indescribable.

v. to cause to separate and go in different directions
v. move away from each other; 
v. separate (light) into spectral rays

n. a curve that reverses the direction of something
n. an aberrant sexual practice; 
n. the action of perverting something (turning it to a wrong use)
